   Baoding, PEOPLES R CHINA, AUG 15-17, 2025},
Organization = {Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers Inc},
Abstract = {The pervasive challenge of Large Language Models (LLMs) hallucinating
   and relying on static knowledge has spurred a critical evolution in AI:
   Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG). This transformative paradigm
   integrates external information retrieval with LLM generation,
   significantly enhancing factual accuracy, timeliness, and domain
   specificity. RAG transforms LLMs into dynamic, verifiable systems. This
   paper comprehensively surveys RAG's core principles, architectural
   advancements, challenges, and future directions, including multimodal
   and agentic RAG, providing a foundational understanding of its immense
   potential in developing more reliable and adaptive AI.},
