   Computing-COLLABTECH-Annual, Universitas Indonesia Timur, Jakarta,
   INDONESIA, NOV 04-07, 2025},
Organization = {Information Processing Society of Japan},
Abstract = {Dialogue-style learning materials are superior to lecture-style learning
   materials in many aspects. However, creating dialogue-style learning
   materials places a significant burden on teachers. In this paper, we
   propose a generative AI system that applies Knowledge Graph-based
   Retrieval-Augmented Generation (KG-RAG) for creating dialogue-style
   learning materials. The initial evaluation suggested that the KG-RAG
   approach has the potential to generate consistent and educationally
   appropriate dialogues, even when high-quality existing teaching
   materials are not available. These findings indicate that KG-RAG may
   offer a promising direction for producing dialogue-style materials in
   resource-scarce contexts, potentially reducing instructor workload while
   maintaining pedagogical value.},
