Year = {2024},
Volume = {14658},
Pages = {3-19},
Note = {28th Pacific-Asia Conference on Knowledge Discovery and Data Mining
   (PAKDD), Taipei, TAIWAN, MAY 07-10, 2024},
Abstract = {This study presents a comprehensive evaluation of Microsoft Research's
   Orca 2, a small yet potent language model, in the context of Retrieval
   Augmented Generation (RAG). The research involved comparing Orca 2 with
   other significant models such as Llama-2, GPT-3.5-Turbo, and GPT-4,
   particularly focusing on its application in RAG. Key metrics, included
   faithfulness, answer relevance, overall score, and inference speed, were
   assessed. Experiments conducted on high-specification PCs revealed Orca
   2's exceptional performance in generating high quality responses and its
   efficiency on consumer-grade GPUs, underscoring its potential for
   scalable RAG applications. This study highlights the pivotal role of
   smaller, efficient models like Orca 2 in the advancement of
   conversational AI and their implications for various IT infrastructures.
   The source codes and datasets of this paper are accessible here
   (https:// github.com/inflaton/Evaluation-of-Orca-2-for-RAG.).},
