Organization = {Association for Computing Machinery},
Abstract = {In this paper, we introduce an end-to-end framework for generating video
   soundtracks that enhances content alignment and controllability compared
   to existing approaches. Leveraging a video-language model (VLM) to
   interpret video semantics and retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) to
   extract compatible style and tempo cues from a music corpus, our
   framework conditions a large language model (LLM) to guide a music
   generator in producing high-fidelity soundtracks. Evaluations across
   diverse video genres demonstrate superior semantic alignment and
   rhythmic synchronization, as well as the framework's effectiveness and
   generalizability. Project page:
