Abstract = {The application of Large Language Models (LLMs) and Retrieval-Augmented
   Generation (RAG) systems in the telecommunication domain presents unique
   challenges, primarily due to the complex nature of telecom standard
   documents and the rapid evolution of the field. The paper introduces
   Telco-RAG,1 an open-source RAG framework designed to handle the specific
   needs of telecommunications standards, particularly 3rd Generation
   Partnership Project (3GPP) documents. Telco-RAG addresses the critical
   challenges of implementing a RAG pipeline on highly technical content,
   paving the way for applying LLMs in telecommunications and offering
   guidelines for RAG implementation in other technical domains.},
