   INFOCOM WKSHPS},
Series = {IEEE Conference on Computer Communications Workshops},
Year = {2025},
Note = {2025 Conference on Computer Communications-INFOCOM-Annual, London,
   ENGLAND, MAY 19-22, 2025},
Organization = {Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers Inc},
Abstract = {The telecommunications industry shift toward disaggregated networks has
   driven the adoption of Open Radio Access Network (O-RAN) architecture.
   While O-RAN offers enhanced flexibility, its implementation presents
   significant challenges in system integration and maintenance,
   particularly due to multi-vendor component compatibility requirements.
   To address these operational complexities, we present the O-RAN
   Assistant, an AI-driven solution built on the Retrieval Augmented
   Generation (RAG) framework. The system is well trained using various
   O-RAN references and leveraging a knowledge base compiled from 35
   authoritative documents. It encompasses deployment protocols,
   maintenance procedures, security frameworks, 6G integration, and
   standardization guidelines. System performance is evaluated across three
   key metrics: groundedness, relevance, and standalone operational
   capability, ensuring reliable assistance in O-RAN deployment and
   maintenance scenarios.},
