Year = {2026},
Volume = {196},
Month = {JUN},
Abstract = {Artificial intelligence-based molecular property prediction plays a
   crucial role in designing bioactive molecules and functional materials.
   However, current methods struggle with challenges such as insufficient
   semantic infor mation, lack of physical knowledge integration, and a
   focus on single-level modeling that ignores the multi-level (atom, bond,
   substructure and molecule) characteristics of molecules. To address
   these issues, this study pro poses MolFSPK, a Dual-Stage Learning
   Framework Fusing Semantic and Physical Knowledge for Molecular Property
   Prediction. It is distinguished by the three features. MolFSPK first
   employs the Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) technique to ensure the
   precision and completeness of molecular semantic information, en hancing
   Large Language Models (LLMs) and mitigating issues such as
   hallucinations and outdated knowledge.},
