   RFID-TA},
Series = {International Conference on RFID Technology and Applications},
Year = {2025},
Note = {15th International Conference on RFID Technology and Applications-RFID
   TA, FRANCE, OCT 28-31, 2025},
Organization = {Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers Inc},
Abstract = {One of the key challenges in deploying large language models (LLMs) is
   hallucination, where models generate fluent but incorrect information.
   Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) addresses this by grounding LLM
   outputs in external sources. However, retrieving from the open web often
   results in varying data quality, making accurate responses about
   specific products difficult. We propose an LLM agent architecture and
   implementation that utilizes GS1 Digital Link-a web-based standard
   converting product identifiers into globally resolvable URLs-to enhance
   response accuracy. By integrating the GS1 Digital Link Resolver, the
   agent accesses authoritative resources linked to product identifiers and
   prioritizes the most relevant links as inputs to a RAG pipeline. This
   structured approach ensures more reliable and context-specific
   responses, demonstrating the synergy between structured identifiers and
   retrieval-augmented language modeling},
