Note = {23rd EPIA Conference on Artificial Intelligence-EPIA, Viana do Castelo,
   PORTUGAL, SEP 03-06, 2024},
Organization = {Polytechnic Institute of Viana do Castelo},
Abstract = {Smart homes are starting to become more present in our daily lives.
   Smart homes are useful for enabling energy management services and
   reducing monetary costs of the consumers. Despite the increasing
   research in these aspects of the smart home, few actually have in mind
   the interactivity of the system they propose. Therefore, this paper, an
   extension of a previous work, proposes a new human-machine interface
   based on multi-agent systems and natural language models with
   retrieval-augmented generation techniques for smart homes to facilitate
   the consumers adaptation to this type of systems. The assistant enables
   the user to control the house and provides him with the information he
   needs, even when a problem within the system occurs. Through the
   experiment the assistant showed to be flexible, able to provide answers
   to questions outside of the smart home system domain and it increases
   the scalability of the system.},
